Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Casa Grande, Pomalca, Relapasa, Maple

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-02-28T21:25:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/peru-stocks-buenaventura-casa-grande-pomalca-relapasa-maple.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose for a third session, gaining
0.3 percent to 22,842.96. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose
0.2 percent to 3,098.21.  Gold miners rose after the precious metal gained in New
York, capping the best monthly increase since April, said
Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.    Rio Alto Mining Ltd . (RIO PE), a Canadian gold exploration
company, advanced 2.6 percent to $2.37.  Minera IRL Ltd . (MIRL
PE), a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, rose 2.1
percent to $1.43. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the
country’s biggest precious-metals miner, gained 1.3 percent to
$46.10.  Sugar producers gained after prices rose for a third
session in  New York  on concern over global supplies.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of
Grupo Oviedo, jumped 6.3 percent to 68 centimos. Casa Grande
(CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of
Gloria SA, rose 1.7 percent to 17.19 soles.  Fuel refiners gained after natural gas advanced in New York
on forecasts for cooler weather.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Spain’s
Repsol YPF SA, rose 2.6 percent to 2 soles. Maple Energy Plc.
(MPLE PE), the oil and natural gas producer with operations in
Peru, rose for the first session in six, gaining 1.9 percent to
$1.06.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  